"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the library scikit-learn because the OneHotEncoder in the ColumnTransformer will output an array with more features than the original DataFrame. GaussianNB in scikit-learn does not support categorical features encoded as multiple columns. It expects a single column per feature.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n< ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n---\\n> ('algo', GaussianNB()) is not the issue here. The issue lies in the encoding.\\n> We can use the following patch to fix the issue:\\n25a26,27\\n> ('selector', SelectFromModel(ExtraTreesClassifier())),\\n> ('algo', GaussianNB()) is not needed here.\\nBut we can use any other classifier here like\\n25c25,26\\n< ('prep', preprocessor),\\n---\\n> ('prep', preprocessor),\\n> ('selector', SelectFromModel(ExtraTreesClassifier())), is not needed here.\\nWe can simply use any other classifier that supports multiple columns per feature like\\n26c26\\n< ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n---\\n> ('algo', RandomForestClassifier())\"\n}"